const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: '€260-400', annual: '€3,120-4,800' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: '€360-530', annual: '€4,320-6,360' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: '€480-720', annual: '€5,760-8,640' },
  { category: 'Estonian Public Healthcare', monthly: '13% payroll', annual: 'Contribution-based' },
  { category: 'Estonian Private Clinic', monthly: '€50-150', annual: '€600-1,800' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Estonia 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Estonia. E-Residency, digital society, Tallinn hospitals, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Estonia"
  subheadline="Estonia offers the world's most advanced digital society, affordable Baltic living, and EU membership—with interesting options for digitally-minded retirees."
  heroImage="/images/countries/estonia-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Estonia</h2>
  <p>
    Estonia is the world's most digitally advanced society—e-government, digital ID, online voting, and efficient bureaucracy. For tech-savvy retirees, it offers unique appeal. The country combines Nordic efficiency with Baltic affordability, plus EU membership and Schengen access.
  </p>

  <p>
    Tallinn's Old Town is a UNESCO World Heritage site with medieval charm and modern amenities. Tartu offers university culture and a more local feel. The coast provides beaches and spa towns. The countryside features forests, bogs, and peaceful rural life.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Good quality; improving rapidly</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Estonian; Russian common; English growing</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> €1,200-2,200/month; affordable by EU standards</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Baltic; cold winters, mild summers</li>
      <li><strong>EU Status:</strong> Full EU member (Eurozone; uses EUR)</li>
      <li><strong>Digital:</strong> World's most advanced e-government</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Estonia's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Estonia's public healthcare is funded through the Estonian Health Insurance Fund (Haigekassa), financed by social tax on employment. Quality has improved significantly since EU accession. Tallinn has modern hospitals including North Estonia Medical Centre and East Tallinn Central Hospital.
  </p>

  <p>
    Private healthcare is growing. Wait times in public system can be weeks for specialists. Private clinics (Confido, Medicum) offer faster access at reasonable prices. Many services can be booked online—Estonia's digital efficiency extends to healthcare.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">E-Residency vs Physical Residence</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Estonia's famous e-Residency does NOT provide physical residence rights or healthcare access. It's for digital business only. To actually live in Estonia and access healthcare, you need proper physical residence—either through EU rights, family, work, or business.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Estonia offers several pathways for retirees:
  </p>

  <h3>Temporary Residence (Sufficient Income)</h3>
  <p>
    Estonia allows residence for those with "sufficient legal income" (typically €1,200+/month). Must demonstrate you won't be a burden on social system. Requires comprehensive health insurance. Renewable annually, leads to long-term residence.
  </p>

  <h3>Digital Nomad Visa (for Active Retirees)</h3>
  <p>
    If you have remote work or freelance income, Estonia's digital nomad visa provides 12-month residence. Requires €4,500/month income and health insurance. Good for active retirees with consulting or remote work.
  </p>

  <h3>EU/EEA Citizens</h3>
  <p>
    Free movement applies. Register with Police and Border Guard Board after 90 days. Must demonstrate sufficient resources and health coverage. After registration, can access Estonian healthcare if contributing.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Estonia:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Residence application:</strong> Comprehensive health insurance required</li>
    <li><strong>EU citizens:</strong> EHIC initially; can join Estonian system if working</li>
    <li><strong>After residence:</strong> Can access public if employed/self-employed</li>
    <li><strong>Retirees:</strong> International insurance often best option</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Estonia</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance is essential for residence applications. Estonia's public healthcare requires social tax contributions (typically through employment). For retirees not working, international insurance remains primary coverage. Estonian private clinics are affordable for out-of-pocket routine care.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Estonia, these providers offer good value:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Estonia</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Good European network, accepted for residence</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Competitive Baltic region pricing</li>
    <li><strong>Estonian Private:</strong> Confido, Medicum for local care at low cost</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage and pricing from providers that accept seniors for Estonia.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Estonia are among the EU's lowest:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Private Estonian:</strong> Confido consultations from €50; very affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> €5,000+ deductible reduces international premiums</li>
    <li><strong>Self-employment:</strong> Registering as self-employed allows public system access</li>
    <li><strong>Direct pay:</strong> Estonian private care is cheap enough to pay cash</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Tech Retiree, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $3,500/month pension. Does occasional consulting. Moving to Tallinn.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Digital Nomad Visa initially (consulting income). Cigna Global for visa. Use Confido for local care.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Cigna ~€350/month. After registering business: Estonian public + Cigna (Estonia excluded) ~€300/month.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Finnish EU Citizen, 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Moving from Helsinki to Tallinn (common route). Finnish pension €1,800/month.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> EU rights apply. Register, access Estonian healthcare. Ferry back to Helsinki for Finnish care as needed.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Estonian public access + Allianz for Finland ~€280/month. Very affordable.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: British Digital Writer, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Post-Brexit, writes online. Income £2,000/month. Attracted by digital society.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Sufficient income residence. BUPA Global required for visa. Register Estonian business for public access option.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA ~€450/month initially. After business: Estonian public + BUPA (Estonia excluded) ~€350/month.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Does e-Residency give me healthcare access?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        No. E-Residency is purely digital—it lets you run an Estonian business remotely. It provides no physical residence rights, no visa, no healthcare access. To actually live in Estonia and access services, you need proper physical residence through other pathways.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How digital is Estonia really?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Extremely. Bank accounts, tax filing, voting, medical records, prescriptions—almost everything is online. Digital ID is used everywhere. Government services are efficient and fast. It's genuinely the world's most advanced digital society. Tech-savvy seniors thrive here.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Estonian hard to learn?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—Estonian is Finno-Ugric (related to Finnish), not Indo-European. It's challenging for English speakers. However, English is widely spoken in Tallinn, especially among younger Estonians. Russian is also common (25% of population). Many expats manage with English.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How cold are Estonian winters?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Cold but manageable. Tallinn averages -5°C in winter, occasionally dropping to -20°C. Less extreme than Finland. Days are short (6 hours daylight in December). Buildings are well-heated. Baltic coast means slightly milder than inland. Prepare for winter driving conditions.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers that specialize in senior expat coverage for Estonia.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Estonian authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
